Only if he'd come 500 or more years earlier.

OTL, the Huns failed in Europe because *everyone* teamed up to fight
them.  The Roman Empire was practically in ruins already, but all the
local barbarians joined in on Rome's side, and the Christian Church
blessed them all.

I'll take this question as:  What if a barbarian mega-migration had come
into Europe, at a time when the Roman Republic still had rivals in the
Mediterranean basin?  Say, during the 1st century BC, at about the time
of Sertorius, Spartacus, Mithridates of Pontus, and the pirate fleets?
Somehow I think not everyone fights against the barbarians in this one.

